layerGroup.name: GEOMORPH_BeagleAMP_surfaceMorphology
layerGroup.title: Seabed surface morphology of the Beagle AMP - multi-scale resolution
layerGroup.abstractTxt: Bathymetric high and low surface morphology of the Beagle Australian Marine Park (AMP). This layer group comprises a surface morphology classification visualised across three levels of scale: broadscale, medium-scale, and finescale. Layers are arranged hierarchically, with broadscale morphology serving as the background layer and finescale positioned as the top layer. Zoom-based styling progressively switches on more detailed layers as zoom level increases.
